36 order issued by an agency of the Department to abate or remediate a
37 violation of any program administered by the agency.
38 b. During the tax year in which the activity occurred for which a credit is
39 being claimed or in the prior two tax years, any of the following:
40 1. A finding was made by the Department of Environmental
41 Quality that the taxpayer knowingly and willfully, as defined
42 in G.S. 143-215.6B, including all limitations thereto,
43 committed a violation of any program implemented by an
44 agency of the Department.
45 2. An assessment for damages to fish or wildlife pursuant to
46 G.S. 143-215.3(a)(7) was made against the taxpayer.
47 3. A judicial order for injunctive relief was issued against the
48 taxpayer in connection with a violation of any program
49 implemented by an agency of the Department of
50 Environmental Quality.
