General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 If, in one of the years in which the installment of a credit accrues, the job with respect to which
2 the credit was claimed is moved to an area in a lower-numbered development tier or an urban
3 progress zone, a port enhancement zone, or an agrarian growth zone, the remaining installments
4 of the credit shall be calculated as if the job had been created initially in the area to which it was
5 moved.
6 (f) Wage Standard. – For the purposes of this section, a taxpayer satisfies the wage
7 standard requirement of G.S. 105-129.83 only if the taxpayer satisfies the requirement with
8 respect to both the new jobs, considered collectively, for which a credit is claimed and all of the
9 jobs at the establishment, considered collectively, with respect to which a credit is claimed.
10 (g) No Double Credit. – A taxpayer may not claim a credit under this section with respect
11 to jobs for which a taxpayer claims a credit under G.S. 105-129.8.
12 "§ 105-129.88. (See notes) Credit for investing in business property.
13 (a) General Credit. – A taxpayer that meets the eligibility requirements set out in
14 G.S. 105-129.83 and that has purchased or leased business property and placed it in service in
15 this State during the taxable year and that has satisfied the threshold requirements of subsection
16 (c) of this section is allowed a credit equal to the applicable percentage of the excess of the
17 eligible investment amount over the applicable threshold. If the taxpayer places business property
18 in service in an urban progress zone, a port enhancement zone, or an agrarian growth zone, the
19 applicable percentage is the one for a development tier one area. Business property is eligible if
20 it is not leased to another party. The credit may not be taken for the taxable year in which the
21 business property is placed in service but shall be taken in equal installments over the four years
22 following the taxable year in which it is placed in service. The applicable percentage is as
23 follows:
24 Area Development Tier Applicable Percentage
25 Tier One 7%
26 Tier Two 5%
27 Tier Three 3.5%
28 (b) Eligible Investment Amount. – The eligible investment amount is the lesser of (i) the
29 cost of the eligible business property and (ii) the amount by which the cost of all of the taxpayer's
30 eligible business property that is in service in this State on the last day of the taxable year exceeds
31 the cost of all of the taxpayer's eligible business property that was in service in this State on the
32 last day of the base year. The base year is that year, of the three immediately preceding taxable
33 years, in which the taxpayer had the most eligible business property in service in this State.
34 (c) Threshold. – The applicable threshold is the appropriate amount set out in the
35 following table based on the development tier where the eligible business property is placed in
36 service during the taxable year. If the taxpayer places business property in service in an urban
37 progress zone, a port enhancement zone, or an agrarian growth zone, the applicable threshold is
38 the one for a development tier one area. Business property placed in service in an urban progress
39 zone, a port enhancement zone, or an agrarian growth zone is not aggregated with business
40 property placed in service at any other eligible establishments regardless of county. If the
41 taxpayer places eligible business property in service at more than one establishment in a county
42 during the taxable year, the threshold applies to the aggregate amount of eligible business
43 property placed in service during the taxable year at all establishments in the county. If the
44 taxpayer places eligible business property in service at establishments in different counties, the
45 threshold applies separately to the aggregate amount of eligible business property placed in
46 service in each county. If the taxpayer places eligible business property in service at an
47 establishment over the course of a two-year period, the applicable threshold for the second
48 taxable year is reduced by the eligible investment amount for the previous taxable year.
49 Area Development Tier Threshold
50 Tier One $ -0-
51 Tier Two 1,000,000
